  "body": "Currently, we represent `Slot` and `Epoch` as a `number`, even though it is defined as a `Uint64`. In practice this has been ok,because we start from 0 and increment these values slowly.\r\n\r\nOne wrinkle to that assumption, `FAR_FUTURE_EPOCH`.We get around that by representing it as `infinity`.\r\n\r\nWe've also had pain running ssz spec tests and fuzz tests that exercise the higher bits of epoch and slot.\r\n\r\nWe'd like to explore changing these types from `number` to `bigint`.",
